'''Sürmene knife'''. Being 15–20&nbsp;cm in height, Sürmene knife has sharp or round tip and the section between incisive part and handle is embroidered by carving. Built in [[Sürmene]] at least since [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]] times.<ref>[[Özhan Öztürk]]. Karadeniz Ansiklopedik Sözlük. İstanbul, 2005 [http://www.karalahana.com/karadeniz/surmene-bicagi.htm Sürmene bıçağı]</ref> [[File:Sürmene knife.jpg|thumb| Traditional Sürmene knives. Steel body, [[silver]] ornaments, handle made from ox [[horn (anatomy)|horn]] and sheath made from [[Buxus|boxwood]]. [[Laz people]] and [[Pontians]] generally use it for duel fighting and knife [[horon]] (dance) since from old times. The little one is used for peeling fruits.]]
